    • Method Detail

      • engine

        TestSuite.Typed.ModelingEngine engine()
        Generates test suite based on a model class given to TestSuite.Typed.ModelingEngine.Factory.create(Class) and returns this object.

        If test generation is already finished in advance, i.e., in a constructor of the implementation, this method will return this object itself and does nothing else.

        Users of ModelingEngine interface must guarantee that this method is called before calling any other methods in this interface.

      • getFactorSpace

        com.github.dakusui.jcunit.core.factor.FactorSpace getFactorSpace()
        Returns a factor space which is extracted from a model class and created by this TestSuite.Typed.ModelingEngine.

      • getTestCases

        List<? extends TestCase> getTestCases()
        Returns test cases generated by this modeling engine.

      • createRunners

        List<? extends org.junit.runner.Runner> createRunners()
        Creates and returns a list of test runners that execute test cases in this test suite.

        Each element in the returned list can be run by following code fragment.

        Result result = new JUnitCore().run(eachElement);
